710601f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 22nd Street (West)
710601f-a.text:
Eleventh Avenue, east side, (buildings thereon, across the
center)from W. 22nd (rieht) to 23rd (1oft) Streets, as viewed
in an eastward direction on W. 22nd Street from Thirteenth
Avenue. In the center, beyond the ramp of the West Side Express
Highway appears a low peaked structure with an anchor decoration.
This is occupied by the New York Port Society and bears No. 166-8
Eleventh Avenue. To the right of these views is the American
Line pier and to the left an open park between 22nd and 23rd
Streets.
Mav 15, 1931.
Views 1 and 2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTI0SS.

710602f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 22nd Street
710602f-a.text:
Eleventh Avenue at 23rd Street seen from 22nd Street near Thirteenth
Avenue across a small park. Because of the clear day, a very
good view of the Empire State Building, Fifth Avenue at 34th
Street, is given.
Summer, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
Neg. ~ 2678

710604f-b.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 22nd Street (West)
710604f-b.text:
(1)
Eleventh Avenue at the North east corner of W.22nd Street,
showing building of the New York Port Society,adjoining
the corner.
March 12th,1929
(2)
Eleventh Avenue at the south west corner of W.23rd Street,
howing the elevated express Ramp and in back-ground the
warehouses at 962 of the Metropolitan Mercantile Marine Co.
September 12th,1931
(3)
Eleventh Avenue at the north east corner,between 24-25th
Streets,showing in the foreground the Moore Bros.,Lumber
Office and adjoining the Royal Card and Paper Co.building.
December 5th,1936
P.L.Sperr,
No reproductions.
